{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0dca09ae-9017-49d7-b532-9ade688cda45","content":"In .NET MAUI, use the **lifecycle events API** in your `MauiProgram.cs` (or anywhere you configure the app builder):\n\n```csharp\nbuilder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>\n{\n#if ANDROID\n    events.AddAndroid(android => android\n        .OnPause(activity =>\n        {\n            // Runs when the activity is pausing\n        })\n        .OnStop(activity =>\n        {\n            // Runs when the activity is no longer visible\n        }));\n#elif IOS\n    events.AddiOS(ios => ios\n        .DidEnterBackground(app =>\n        {\n            // Runs when the app enters the background\n        }));\n#endif\n});\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- Add the NuGet package reference — lifecycle events live in `Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents`.\n- Add `using Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;` at the top.\n- Use `#if ANDROID` / `#elif IOS` preprocessor directives to keep platform code compile-safe.\n- Each platform exposes its native events (e.g., `OnResume`, `OnDestroy` for Android; `WillEnterForeground`, `WillTerminate` for iOS).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"047798cb-1cdf-4e6d-a45d-b1f60138289d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to hook into platform-specific lifecycle events in .NET MAUI, specifically Android's OnPause/OnStop and iOS's DidEnterBackground. This is a general knowledge question about .NET MAUI development — I can answer this directly without needing to search the codebase.","outputTokens":388,"requestId":"7FD0:21AE1A:5EE7D00:67BC206:69F156DE"},"id":"84257b52-4f80-445a-af1b-a48941f371b9","timestamp":"2026-04-29T00:55:02.254Z","parentId":"d28d4fde-14a6-472d-9e07-08b2375b2c14"}
